#: src/rust-2018/trait-system/more-container-types-support-trait-objects.md:1
msgid "More container types support trait objects"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/trait-system/more-container-types-support-trait-objects.md:3
msgid ""
"![Minimum Rust version: 1.2](https://img.shields.io/badge/"
"Minimum%20Rust%20Version-1.2-brightgreen.svg)"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/trait-system/more-container-types-support-trait-objects.md:5
msgid ""
"In Rust 1.0, only certain, special types could be used to create [trait "
"objects](https://doc.rust-lang.org/book/ch17-02-trait-objects.html)."
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/trait-system/more-container-types-support-trait-objects.md:8
msgid ""
"With Rust 1.2, that restriction was lifted, and more types became able to do "
"this. For example, `Rc<T>`, one of Rust's reference-counted types:"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/trait-system/more-container-types-support-trait-objects.md:25
msgid "This code would not work with Rust 1.0, but now works."
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/trait-system/more-container-types-support-trait-objects.md:27
msgid ""
"If you haven't seen the `dyn` syntax before, see [the section on it](dyn-"
"trait-for-trait-objects.md). For versions that do not support it, replace "
"`Rc<dyn Foo>` with `Rc<Foo>`."
msgstr ""
